args: When I was worryin' about how a leader\nshould fight, it was yer words what first\npopped into my head.
Still, bein' the big cheese is a lot\nof pressure, yeah?
This has made me realize just how\namazing you are for leadin' a whole city.
Ya trained me hard since I was a kid,\nbut it was so I could do the same thing.
Too bad I ended up gettin' sick of it all\nand takin' off!
But everything ya taught me stuck in my\nnoggin all this time—and it's helpin' now.
I'm impressed. I see you've broadened\nyour horizons a little.
You used to pay no attention to your\nsurroundings, but it looks like those\ndays are behind you.
...Nah. I still got a long way to go.
But I think I finally see where I need\nto be headin'.
I know what I can do—and should do.
And to do that, I'm gonna...
Cleo made cookies, so we were\nthinking of...having...some...and...\nWow. You look REALLY serious.
Can I borrow ya for a second here,\n{player_name}?
Okay, now you look SUPER serious.
Hang on just a hot minute, bub!\nWhat's going on here?!
Draw yer sword. ...And I mean business.
Ranzal, I don't know what this is about,\nbut I don't want to fight you.
Whoa! That was a serious blow!
Stop it! Stop it right now!
Stay outta this, Notte—or you'll be next.
We last fought back in the forest, yeah?\nOn the day we met?
Show me how much you've grown!
You're serious about this, aren't you?
Ask my sword how serious I am!
If that's the best ya can do, yer pactbound\ndragons must be nothin' more than dogs!
An ancient kingdom falls, an empire takes\nits place, and a new kingdom rises to\nmeet that challenge...
We're livin' in some excitin' times!
There's nothing exciting about people\nsuffering at the hands of fiends and war.
Every man dreams of bein' king\nat least once in his life.
But you? You might just have the power\nto make it happen for real.
And if I use the chaos to my advantage,\nI could rise to power myself!
Maybe I should march into Saint Lotier\nand take it from my pops...
...Or maybe I'll just overthrow you\nand steal THIS country instead!
We built this country together, remember?!\nIt's full of everyone's hopes and dreams!
Are you just forgetting all that?!
I won't hand this country over to you.
I'm going to lead everyone here so we\ncan defeat the Empire together.
If you won't hand it over,\nmaybe I'll just take it!
Bwa ha ha! Okay, what kinda idiot laughs\nin the middle of a deadly duel?
I am SO confused right now.
You were holding back. Weren't you?
Don't get me wrong—there was a lot of\npower behind your sword.
But we've fought side by side, so I know\nyou're capable of far more.
I thought I'd try to train up the prince here\nlike my pops used to do with me.
But I already ran away from that once—\nshould'a known I wasn't cut out for it.
So that's why you were acting so strangely.
Fat lotta good it did, though. This'll teach\nme to think before I just run off and...\ndo stuff. Sorry, {player_name}.
Grrrr! I was WORRIED, you dummy!
You're just a big dumb stupidhead\nuglyface JERKSTORE!
Sorry, Notte. I won't ever do it again.
Fine. Then I guess I forgive you.\n...But you're still a jerkstore.
Guess I'm not cut out to be the great man\nmy pops is. Hell, when I tried, all I ended\nup doin' was makin' Notte mad at me.
The sons of Saint Lotier are meant to\nlive by the sea and with it...
It's a phrase everyone born in Saint Lotier\nknows.
All of her citizens have a duty to protect\ntheir country and that sea—and it's a\nduty we're grateful to have.
Guess I turned my back on that.
You may have left your people behind,\nbut looking at you right now reminds me\nof the vast sea we saw from your home.
So yer sayin' the spirit of the sea\nlives on in ol' Ranzal?
Well, that's swell—but the country I'm\ngonna protect is the one with you in it!
This land is full of sufferin' people,\nand you need to do somethin' about it.
But if you become king, I know you can\nturn all of that pain into happiness.
Forget the sea—you can support the world!
I don't know about all that...
It'll be fine so long as I'm with ya!
And don't forget Notte—\nyour bestest friend ever!
Everyone in this castle is pinnin' their\nhopes on you. Don't forget that.
I know—and I will work hard to meet\ntheir expectations.
Well, I guess you and me still gotta\nwork on surpassin' our pops.
Let's combine our strength to make a\ncountry both our fathers can be proud of!
Bwaaaa ha ha! Ain't that a thing!
